1
00:01:39,380 --> 00:01:45,020
[My Heroic Husband]

2
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:47,960
[Episode 15]

3
00:01:49,519 --> 00:01:53,379
Shouldn't I come up with a name before we start learning from this rare book?

4
00:01:53,379 --> 00:01:54,679
I've already come up with a name for myself.

5
00:01:54,679 --> 00:01:57,359
I would be called "Human Butcher of Bloody Hands."

6
00:01:57,359 --> 00:02:00,318
- Master, you're called...
- Lu Hongti.

7
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,640
You do have a name?

8
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:05,080
Lu Hongti?

9
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,299
That name does sound quite tasty. (Her name has the same characters that also mean red grapes.)

10
00:02:07,299 --> 00:02:09,200
Stop with the nonsense!

11
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:11,219
Master is right in chiding me!

12
00:02:11,219 --> 00:02:15,140
Then let's... Get started.

13
00:02:36,559 --> 00:02:38,359
I've finished teaching.

14
00:02:47,939 --> 00:02:49,539
Master.

15
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:56,639
You're really only teaching it once?

16
00:02:56,639 --> 00:02:59,200
What kind of lousy teacher is she?

17
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,400
[Su Manor]

18
00:03:04,679 --> 00:03:06,379
Three Bamboo Tile.

19
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,740
Green Tile.

20
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,970
I'm sorry.

21
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:24,799
I don't know what is with my daughter and son-in-law.

22
00:03:24,799 --> 00:03:27,090
They insisted on buying these trivial things for me.

23
00:03:27,090 --> 00:03:29,699
It even makes playing Mahjong inconvenient.

24
00:03:29,699 --> 00:03:33,579
I told them that I didn't need these. But she insisted on it.

25
00:03:33,579 --> 00:03:37,759
Sometimes having a daughter that is too filial can also be troublesome, right?

26
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:40,879
That's right. Your son-in-law has such a successful business.

27
00:03:40,879 --> 00:03:44,058
He must be so busy that he doesn't have time to care for Tan'er anymore, right?

28
00:03:44,058 --> 00:03:48,118
If so, then when will you ever have a grandchild?

29
00:03:48,118 --> 00:03:50,678
It's also good that Madame doesn't have any grandchildren.

30
00:03:50,678 --> 00:03:53,539
She's able to still have time to play Mahjong with you, right?

31
00:03:53,539 --> 00:03:56,159
My eldest grandson is extremely clingy.

32
00:03:56,159 --> 00:03:57,580
He is unable to be without someone even for a single day.

33
00:03:57,580 --> 00:04:00,118
He has been making an uproar with me wanting a rattle these two days.

34
00:04:00,118 --> 00:04:03,519
Oh, that's right, do you know which long-standing shop makes the best rattles?

35
00:04:03,519 --> 00:04:06,518
I want to buy one to play with him later. That way I can avoid him making a fuss at home every day.

36
00:04:06,518 --> 00:04:07,599
I know. I know.

37
00:04:07,599 --> 00:04:10,199
There is a store that is good at making these gadgets.

38
00:04:10,199 --> 00:04:11,919
My granddaughter really likes their gadgets.

39
00:04:11,919 --> 00:04:13,100
- Really?
- Yes!

40
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:15,440
- Are there a lot of different patterns and styles?
- Yes!

41
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:17,499
Are we still playing Mahjong?

42
00:04:19,559 --> 00:04:20,998
Yes, let's continue playing.

43
00:04:20,998 --> 00:04:22,238
Yes. Come on.

44
00:04:22,238 --> 00:04:24,039
I am not going to play any longer!

45
00:04:24,039 --> 00:04:26,160
Why are you not playing anymore?

46
00:04:27,940 --> 00:04:31,879
The waterproof paint invented by Young Master deserves to become renowned in Jiangning.

47
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:35,238
In Lin'an, even Shuwan responded without delay after hearing about it.

48
00:04:35,238 --> 00:04:37,078
She came looking for me to ask for the paint formula.

49
00:04:37,078 --> 00:04:39,640
Then is Young Lady planning to give it to Miss Lou?

50
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:43,758
If it was only Shuwan, I would've naturally granted her request.

51
00:04:43,758 --> 00:04:46,638
However, those people in the Lou Family often bully her.

52
00:04:46,638 --> 00:04:51,459
I'm afraid that by giving her the formula I would be helping someone else succeed.

53
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:55,659
My good daughter. Look at you!

54
00:04:55,659 --> 00:05:00,420
Can't you let me gain some respect in front of others?

55
00:05:00,420 --> 00:05:03,338
Mother, you've already been wearing so many pieces of jewelry.

56
00:05:03,338 --> 00:05:06,318
You still can't hold your head high in front of others?

57
00:05:06,318 --> 00:05:08,118
Hold my head high?

58
00:05:08,118 --> 00:05:10,839
I can hardly hold my head up. It's heavy.

59
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:13,470
What can I even use all these things for?

60
00:05:13,470 --> 00:05:15,100
I want to have a grandchild.

61
00:05:15,100 --> 00:05:16,830
A grandchild!

62
00:05:16,839 --> 00:05:20,198
What have you and your husband done here every night?

63
00:05:20,198 --> 00:05:23,379
Are you just lying on your stomach working through the account books? Can't you...

64
00:05:28,879 --> 00:05:30,599
Young Lady.

65
00:05:30,599 --> 00:05:33,138
Mother. Mother.

66
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:37,160
Mother. Mother.

67
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:38,499
This…

68
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:46,018
This… This…this…this… This hole! What is this?

69
00:05:52,380 --> 00:05:55,799
So turns out you and your husband have been sleeping in separate rooms.

70
00:05:55,799 --> 00:05:58,479
No wonder you have no signs of being pregnant.

71
00:05:58,480 --> 00:06:01,619
You're driving me crazy. When can I have a grandchild?

72
00:06:01,619 --> 00:06:04,319
You can't do this to me.

73
00:06:07,420 --> 00:06:09,619
It's no use in just scolding me.

74
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:13,539
I can't decide myself on this kind of matter.

75
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:18,398
Okay. Today, I'll decide for you.

76
00:06:18,398 --> 00:06:22,259
Xiao Chan, go and tear down Ning Yi's room!

77
00:06:22,259 --> 00:06:23,638
I'll see where he sleeps in the future!

78
00:06:23,638 --> 00:06:26,298
- Tear-Tear down...
- Go! Right now!

79
00:06:26,298 --> 00:06:28,778
- Tear down whatever you see, the table, stools, chairs and the cabinet.
- Madam. I…

80
00:06:28,778 --> 00:06:31,500
Tear them all down! Don't leave anything intact!

81
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:33,318
I just won't believe

82
00:06:33,318 --> 00:06:36,780
that if it is all torn down that he wouldn't sleep here. Where else would he sleep?

83
00:06:37,379 --> 00:06:39,338
Young Lady.

84
00:06:39,338 --> 00:06:42,658
Xiao Chan, my mother is already this angry.

85
00:06:42,658 --> 00:06:45,300
I can't do anything about it.

86
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:46,619
Tear them down.

87
00:06:46,619 --> 00:06:48,420
Understood!

88
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:45,080
Was there an earthquake?

89
00:07:45,879 --> 00:07:47,979
It can't be.

90
00:07:47,979 --> 00:07:50,600
An earthquake only in this room?

91
00:07:53,119 --> 00:07:56,279
Forget it. I'd better hurry and fix this.

92
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:31,019
This… Why is Young Master so persistant?

93
00:08:31,019 --> 00:08:32,998
I tore it down once and he fixed it back up once.

94
00:08:32,998 --> 00:08:35,959
He doesn't find it tiring, but I do.

95
00:08:46,939 --> 00:08:49,159
I just won't believe it!

96
00:08:49,159 --> 00:08:51,939
Young Master. Young Master.

97
00:08:51,939 --> 00:08:54,578
Young Master. Young Master. Young Master.

98
00:08:54,578 --> 00:08:57,539
It's like your room has been haunted these few days. The things in your room keep breaking.

99
00:08:57,539 --> 00:08:59,198
There's too much for me to fix.

100
00:08:59,198 --> 00:09:00,958
What you are doing is covering up your own misdeeds by shifting the blame onto other people.

101
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:02,879
I seriously suspect that you are the one doing it!

102
00:09:02,879 --> 00:09:04,958
You're doing this to get me to hurry and write novels, right?

103
00:09:04,958 --> 00:09:09,139
If I wanted to urge you to write more, I could just directly beat you. Why would I have to tear down your room?

104
00:09:09,139 --> 00:09:11,239
You really might not be able to defeat me now.

105
00:09:11,239 --> 00:09:13,679
I've done some practice. I also…

106
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:19,079
It hurts, it hurts!

107
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:21,380
Let's go.

108
00:09:45,599 --> 00:09:49,558
Oh no! Not again! This time the roof is leaking.

109
00:09:49,558 --> 00:09:52,780
Young Master, now do you see?

110
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:56,998
We've been staying together for this whole time. I couldn't have done this.

111
00:09:57,520 --> 00:10:01,119
It wasn't you. It was the ghost.

112
00:10:02,319 --> 00:10:03,519
Forget it.

113
00:10:03,519 --> 00:10:07,838
Even if a ghost comes, it only goes to my room. Don't be afraid.

114
00:10:07,838 --> 00:10:09,480
That's right.

115
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:13,899
Young Master, I'll go find a ladder and fix it for you.

116
00:10:33,020 --> 00:10:35,318
- You smashed everything?
- I did.

117
00:10:35,318 --> 00:10:38,438
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

118
00:10:56,279 --> 00:10:59,100
Young Lady, there are already two holes in Young Master's room.

119
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:01,000
Why hasn't he come here yet?

120
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,600
How about you go back first?

121
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:05,000
I'll wait for him here alone.

122
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,600
- My Lady, are you planning to…
- Why are you still here?

123
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:22,600
How long does one have to practice to reach the point of destroying the roof?

124
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:38,200
Young Lady, my legs are numb.

125
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,000
Mine, too.

126
00:11:43,990 --> 00:11:46,090
[Su Manor]

127
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,500
Everyone be quiet and gentle.

128
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,400
Don't startle Young Lady.

129
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:53,900
My Lady.

130
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:55,900
Hurry up. Hurry.

131
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:00,400
Hurry up. Follow up.

132
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,300
Hurry up.

133
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,100
Catch up.

134
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:06,800
Be defter!

135
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,600
Everyone be deft! Defter!

136
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,400
Don't procrastinate!

137
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,100
Everyone be very careful!

138
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:16,400
The weather is very dry.

139
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,200
We have to guard against things catching fire.

140
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:20,600
The Second Master's room was burned one time before.

141
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:23,200
The Elder Master had no choice but to take in Young Master Wenxing.

142
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,500
They were crammed living together.

143
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:26,000
It was tough for the Elder Master.

144
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,800
A thing like that cannot happen in our First Master's.

145
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:32,500
Xiao Chan, where did Young Master go?

146
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:53,300
My Lady? My Lady?

147
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,000
Master. Master.

148
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,500
It's me. It's me.

149
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:23,200
Your strikes are ruthless enough.

150
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:24,900
Even a vicious tiger will not eat its cubs.

151
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:27,300
In any case, I'm your only disciple.

152
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:32,600
Originally when you gave me a rare book, I was happily learning from it.

153
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,300
I thought that I had mastered it.

154
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:37,500
I didn't expect that I would still be defeated by you in a few moves.

155
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:43,000
But… I saw what you were doing just now.

156
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:46,500
Your heroes are always doing useless things and never anything proper.

157
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:49,800
Also you like to send letters with pigeons.

158
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,700
What kind of letter is that?

159
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:54,000
A love letter?

160
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,400
You can tell me.

161
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,200
I can even teach you...

162
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:01,700
All right.

163
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:04,000
This joke is not funny.

164
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,600
I know what you just sent.

165
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,600
A confidential letter. Right?

166
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:12,600
Heroes like you must have undertaken some type of mission.

167
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:16,800
Of course, I don't want to know what it is specifically.

168
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:19,700
The reason why you assassinated Song Xian has nothing to do with me.

169
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:22,000
In Jiangning, I currently

170
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,500
have a family, relatives, and friends.

171
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:28,800
As long as you don't hurt them, we'll live in peace with each other.

172
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,200
Let me count it for you.

173
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:33,200
As long as… you don't hurt my wife,

174
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:37,300
Lao Geng, Xiao Chan, my father-in-law,

175
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:41,400
my mother-in-law, Li Pin, Gao Qiu, Feng Yuan…

176
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,100
There are so many people you want to protect.

177
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:44,300
It's good that you know.

178
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:48,200
In short, we both keep out of each other's affairs, then we can continue being friends.

179
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,000
Do you understand?

180
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,400
You have misunderstood.

181
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:53,000
Everything I do is for the desire to rid evils from the people

182
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,200
and bring justice to this world.

183
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:59,800
You heroes always like saying these kinds of pretentious words.

184
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:01,800
It doesn't matter. You don't want to tell the truth

185
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:03,600
and I am too lazy to ask.

186
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:05,800
This is the truth.

187
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,900
Nowaday, the Wu Dynasty has to bow its head to Liang and Jing.

188
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:09,200
It's only because the Wu Dynasty has lowered its head

189
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,200
that all the people can raise their heads.

190
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,800
But it's not a permanent solution.

191
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,000
Have you ever thought

192
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,600
that someday the Jing State will grow stronger and unruly. They'll definitely go south then.

193
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:19,000
When they have forcefully killed right before the people you want to protect,

194
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,700
you likewise would have to protect this country,

195
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:23,400
because if the country is ruined, the land will still be here

196
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:26,400
but home will truly be gone.

197
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,800
That's pretty good.

198
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:29,700
Your speech is rich with provocation.

199
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:31,200
I nearly fell for your words.

200
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:33,900
Anyway, I still hope for the world to be at peace.

201
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:37,400
It would be best that no country should ever start a fight with other countries.

202
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:40,000
But after listening to your words,

203
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:43,100
I think you're really a good person.

204
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,900
You're really an extraordinary person.

205
00:15:44,900 --> 00:15:49,300
I'm proud to have such a master like you.

206
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,000
Master. Master.

207
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,100
Let go! Let go!

208
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:54,200
I was wrong!

209
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:03,000
Rude!

210
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,800
What're you doing, Lao Geng?

211
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,800
What's Young Lady doing?

212
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:05,600
Preventing fire and cooling down.

213
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:17,200
Young Lady is moving away the splashing tube used for putting out a fire.

214
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:20,000
If there is a fire, what she did

215
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,800
would cause there not to be enough time to put out the fire.

216
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,800
The splashing tube has become old with age.

217
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,800
Young Lady took it for maintaince.

218
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,200
Why is she holding a gourd ladle now?

219
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:10,600
If there is a fire, Young Lady must know

220
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,800
how much water the gourd ladle can contain.

221
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:23,900
She threw out the gourd ladle now?

222
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,400
She knows now

223
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:28,200
that the gourd ladle can't hold too much water.

224
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:30,000
She needs to use a wooden basin.

225
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,100
Now the wooden basin is gone, too.

226
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:46,000
I really can't explain this.

227
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,700
What does she want to do?

228
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:10,600
Young Master, did you offend Young Lady somehow?

229
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:12,400
Nonsense!

230
00:19:13,700 --> 00:19:18,000
All of Young Lady's actions are obviously done to burn down your side room.

231
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,400
She really is going to burn it?

232
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,600
No!

233
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:37,600
Young Master, you won't have a place to sleep if the side room is burnt down.

234
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:39,600
Where will you sleep?

235
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:58,400
She could have just told me

236
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,400
rather than going through all this trouble.

237
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:07,600
Someone come!

238
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,800
Fire!

239
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:10,800
Hurry and put out the fire!

240
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:12,300
Someone come!

241
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:18,200
There's a fire. Put out the fire.

242
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,000
Someone come!

243
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:24,900
There's a fire! Come and put out the fire!

244
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:26,600
I don't know what happened.

245
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:29,800
The weather has been dry. How come the room suddenly caught on fire?

246
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,900
We should put out the fire first.

247
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,798
No hurry.

248
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:35,800
Let it burn for a bit more.

249
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,500
Young Master!

250
00:20:40,100 --> 00:20:42,000
Everyone be careful!

251
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,300
These goods are fine as it is.

252
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:46,500
Don't hurt yourselves!

253
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:49,100
Young Master,

254
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:51,800
did Young Lady do all of this to

255
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:53,800
consummate with you by burning the room?

256
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:56,000
Are the two of you going to...

257
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:13,800
Lao Geng, do you think the fire can be put out now?

258
