406
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:23,900
My dear,

407
00:32:23,900 --> 00:32:27,200
for our honeymoon we can go to the south this time.

408
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:30,200
There would be many fun things to do and delicious foods to try.

409
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,700
What is a honeymoon?

410
00:32:31,700 --> 00:32:34,600
My dear, what you are saying is becoming more and more confusing.

411
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:36,300
The honeymoon…

412
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:40,300
The honeymoon is… After two people are together,

413
00:32:40,300 --> 00:32:42,400
there will be one month during which they want to be with each other most.

414
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:44,400
So, we must go out to have fun.

415
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:46,600
One month that they want to be with each other the most?

416
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:50,200
So afterward, they don't want to be together anymore?

417
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:52,600
Are we going to separate in the future?

418
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:54,500
No way.

419
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:56,200
How could it be possible that we will separate?

420
00:32:56,200 --> 00:32:57,600
Even if we're separated.

421
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,400
I will definitely find you.

422
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:01,800
What if you can't find me?

423
00:33:02,800 --> 00:33:06,100
Sure enough, women like asking these kinds of questions.

424
00:33:06,100 --> 00:33:09,100
How can we be separated during such peaceful times?

425
00:33:09,100 --> 00:33:12,000
Can't we just live life peacefully?

426
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:14,200
It's not possible that I can't find you.

427
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:20,300
Even if you walk to the ends of the earth, I'll stay with you forever.

428
00:33:31,900 --> 00:33:34,700
